From: Сергей Кот <srg91@yandex-team.ru>
Date: Mon, 30 Jan 2023 13:26:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [uwsgi] Calculate max_procname with environ only for Python 3

While using pyuwsgi with python2 we don't allocate memory for environ (pyuwsgi.c:pyuwsgi_set_orig_argv).

Because it's python2 only we don't create issue and PR for original repository.

REVIEW: 3402257

---
diff --git a/core/uwsgi.c b/core/uwsgi.c
--- a/core/uwsgi.c
+++ b/uwsgi.c
@@ -1767,7 +1767,9 @@ static void fixup_argv_and_environ(int argc, char **argv, char **environ, char *
 	for (i = 0; environ[i] != NULL; i++) {
 		// useless
 		//if ((environ[0] + uwsgi.max_procname + 1) == environ[i]) {
+#ifdef PYTHREE
 		uwsgi.max_procname += strlen(environ[i]) + 1;
+#endif
 		//}
 		env_count++;
 	}
